    <title>SBF to get the Girls treatment in Going Infinite film adaptation</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Sam Bankman-Fried is shown against a background of red" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/brYa4Oqiu7AiE6gOKn4FAPQgHY0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73719221/STK_226445_Sam_Bankman_Fried_FTX.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Image: The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="56kMhL"&gt;Apple and A24 are working on a new movie about imprisoned crypto tycoon Sam Bankman-Fried based on &lt;em&gt;The Big Short&lt;/em&gt; writer Michael Lewis's book &lt;em&gt;Going Infinite: The Rise and Fall of a New Tycoon. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://variety.com/2024/film/news/lena-dunham-sam-bankman-fried-movie-apple-a24-michael-lewis-going-infinite-1236207495/"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Variety&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; reported their arrangement and that&lt;em&gt; Girls &lt;/em&gt;creator and star Lena Dunham is set to write the film.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="MIXLWJ"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Going Infinite&lt;/em&gt; is Lewis’s &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/26/23934195/sam-bankman-fried-self-testimony-deleted-signal#:~:text=Michael%20Lewis%2C%20whose%20most%20recent%20book"&gt;chronicle &lt;/a&gt;of the rise, &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2022/11/15/23459268/sam-bankman-fried-ftx-bankruptcy-crypto-lobbying-washington"&gt;spectacular implosion&lt;/a&gt;, and eventual conviction of Bankman-Fried and his crypto exchange FTX. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="c-float-left c-float-hang"&gt;&lt;aside id="ADhov1"&gt;&lt;div data-anthem-component="readmore" data-anthem-component-data='{"stories":[{"title":"Sam Bankman-Fried sentenced to 25 years for FTX fraud","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/28/24112507/sam-bankman-fried-sentence-ftx-alameda"}]}'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/aside&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="HKwwcx"&gt;Lewis was working on the book already and embedded with Bankman-Fried when FTX collapsed in 2022. SBF was ultimately found guilty of several criminal fraud and conspiracy charges and given a &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/28/24112507/sam-bankman-fried-sentence-ftx-alameda"&gt;25-year prison sentence&lt;/a&gt;. He’s appealing his conviction, even as his fellow FTX executives &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/30/24284017/ftx-co-conspirator-nishad-singh-isnt-going-to-prison"&gt;are being sentenced&lt;/a&gt; and...&lt;/p&gt;
